\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 07, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104skw1665702542274.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/skw1665702542274.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/skw1665702542274.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"skw1665702542274\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                       \n TCP Connector Options\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"skw1665702542274__tcp_connector_options_104979\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can assign connector options by setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$TCP_PARAMS</span> in the [DRIVER_SETTINGS] section of the assignment file.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"skw1665702542274__topic_d32198e1_d32199e1_d32200e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$TCP_PARAMS =</code>\n                       {<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ub</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">MaximumPacketSize</var>} {\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">%/</code>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sb</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">MaximumSendBufferKB</var>} {\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">%/</code>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rb</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">MaximumReceiveBufferKB</var>} {\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">%/</code>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">n</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=0</code>\n                       |\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>\n                       } {\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">nl</span>} {\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">%/</code>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">prf</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=4</code>\n                       |\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">6</code>\n                       } {\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">%/</code>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ql</span>=<var class=\"keyword varname\">QueueLength</var> { \n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">, %/</code>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ka</span>}\n      </section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"skw1665702542274__topic_d21197e1_d21198e1_d21199e1_d21200e1_d21201e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d424197e160\">\n                        \n Options\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"skw1665702542274__li_d16721e1_d16722e1_d16723e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ghq1665702542911.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ghq1665702542911.html\" title=\"Enables the keep-alive mechanism, which checks that the TCP socket is still alive by periodically sending a packet to solicit a response from the peer. If a number of such packets are sent without receiving a response, the connection is closed.\">ka</a> (Keep Alive) </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"skw1665702542274__li_d16709e1_d16710e1_d16711e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gsj1665702882214.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gsj1665702882214.html\" title=\"Determines whether the Nagle algorithm is used to bundle data packets into larger network packets before they are sent.\">n</a> (Nagling) </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"skw1665702542274__li_d16712e1_d16713e1_d16714e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"awp1665702882493.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/awp1665702882493.html\" title=\"No linger. Allows TCP sockets to be closed without delay and not enter TIMED_WAIT state.\">nl</a> (No Linger) </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"skw1665702542274__li_d16715e1_d16716e1_d16717e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mwa1665702882785.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mwa1665702882785.html\" title=\"Set the TCP/IP version preference to TCP4 (IPv4) or TCP6 (IPv6).\">prf</a> (Version\n               Preference) </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"skw1665702542274__li_d16718e1_d16719e1_d16720e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nub1665702883086.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nub1665702883086.html\" title=\"Determines the requested queue length, which controls how many concurrent client connection requests can be handled.\">ql</a> (Queue Length) </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"skw1665702542274__li_d16706e1_d16707e1_d16708e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"myl1665702883437.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/myl1665702883437.html\" title=\"Set the maximum size of the TCP receive buffer, in kilobytes.\">rb</a> (Receive\n               Buffer) </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"skw1665702542274__li_d16703e1_d16704e1_d16705e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nng1665702883846.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nng1665702883846.html\" title=\"Set the maximum size of the TCP send buffer, in kilobytes.\">sb</a> (Send Buffer) </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"skw1665702542274__li_d16700e1_d16701e1_d16702e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gjq1665702884133.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gjq1665702884133.html\" title=\"Set the maximum Uniface message buffer, expressed in bytes. Uniface segments the data to be sent into chunks of this size.\">ub</a> (Uniface buffer) </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"skw1665702542274__topic_d21202e1_d21203e1_d21204e1_d21205e1_d21206e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d424197e246\">\n                        \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"skw1665702542274__p_d32207e1_d32208e1_d32209e1\">TCP connector options enable you to tune the TCP connector performance.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"skw1665702542274__p_d32210e1_d32211e1_d32212e1\">The TCP connector creates the physical connection for both TCP/IP and TLS connections. When you set connector options for the TCP connector, these settings stay in effect for all TCP and TLS connections.</p>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[DRIVER_SETTINGS]\nUSYS$TCP_PARAMS = ub=4096, sb=16, n=1, nl\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/msq1665702542189.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>[DRIVER_SETTINGS]</a><p>Use the [DRIVER_SETTINGS] section of the assignment file to specify the database and component engine connectors used, and their parameter options. The options available depend on the connector in use.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532034\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532034\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "TCP Connector Options Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 07, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 TCP Connector Options You can assign connector options by setting USYS$TCP_PARAMS in the [DRIVER_SETTINGS] section of the assignment file. USYS$TCP_PARAMS = { ub = MaximumPacketSize } { , %/ sb = MaximumSendBufferKB } { , %/ rb = MaximumReceiveBufferKB } { , %/ n =0 | 1 } { , nl } { , %/ prf =4 | 6 } { , %/ ql = QueueLength { , %/ ka } Options ka (Keep Alive) n (Nagling) nl (No Linger) prf (Version Preference) ql (Queue Length) rb (Receive Buffer) sb (Send Buffer) ub (Uniface buffer) Description TCP connector options enable you to tune the TCP connector performance. The TCP connector creates the physical connection for both TCP/IP and TLS connections. When you set connector options for the TCP connector, these settings stay in effect for all TCP and TLS connections. [DRIVER_SETTINGS] USYS$TCP_PARAMS = ub=4096, sb=16, n=1, nl Copy Related Links [DRIVER_SETTINGS] Use the [DRIVER_SETTINGS] section of the assignment file to specify the database and component engine connectors used, and their parameter options. The options available depend on the connector in use. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}